ework Guide](/docs/user/microservice)\n    -   [ORM Framework Support](/docs/user/ormframework)\n    -   [Data Source support](/docs/user/datasource)\n    -   [SQL Reference](/docs/user/sqlreference/sql-restrictions)\n        \n    -   [APM](/docs/user/apm/skywalking)\n        \n    -   [Testing Report](/docs/user/performance)\n        \n    -   [Appendix](/docs/user/appendix/global-transaction-status)\n        \n-   Developer Guide\n    \n    -   [Transaction Mode](/docs/dev/mode/at-mode)\n        \n    -   [Domain Model](/docs/dev/domain/overviewDomainModel)\n        \n    -   [Metrics Design](/docs/dev/seata-mertics)\n-   Ops Guide\n    \n    -   [Version Upgrade Guide](/docs/ops/upgrade)\n    -   [Multi-configuration Isolation](/docs/ops/multi-configuration-isolation)\n    -   [Deploy](/docs/ops/deploy-guide-beginner)\n        \n-   Security Guide\n    \n    -   [SecretKey Security](/docs/security/secret-key)\n\n-   [](/)\n-   Overview\n-   FAQ\n\nVersion: v2.6\n\n# FAQ\n\n[1.Can Seata be used in a production environment?](#1)  \n[2.Dose Seata support high availability ?](#2)  \n[3.What is the use of the record of undo log table log status = 1 ?](#3)  \n[4.How to use the Seata framework to ensure transaction isolation?](#4)  \n[5.When Failed to roll back dirty data, what shall I do ?](#5)  \n[6.Why the global transaction state is not \"begin\" when a branch transaction is registered ?](#6)  \n[7.When Nacos is used as the Seata configuration center, the project startup error report cannot find the service. How to check and deal with it ?](#7)  \n[8.When Eureka is the registry and TC is highly available, how to overwrite Eureka properties at the TC end?](#8)  \n[9.java.lang.NoSuchMethodError: com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.jsontype.TypeSerializer.typeId(Ljava/lang/Object;Lcom/fasterxml/jackson/core/JsonToken;)?](#9)  \n[10\\. Why didn't my mybatis operation return auto-generated ID?](#10)  \n[11.I can't find this package:io.seata.codec.protobuf.generated,and cant't run seata server?](#11)  \n[12.How does TC use database drivers such as mysql/oracle?](#12)  \n[13.Support multiple primary keys?](#13)  \n[14.How to solve the error reported by HikariDataSource?](#14)  \n[15.Can I write the configuration directly to application.properties without using the conf type configuration file?](#15)  \n[16.How to package seata-server after modifying the source code?](#16)  \n[17.What RPC frameworks does seata support now?](#17)  \n[18\\. java.lang.NoSuchMethodError: com.alibaba.druid.sql.ast.statement .SQLSelect.getFirstQueueBlockLcom/alibaba/druid/sql/ast/statement/SQLSelectQueryBlock;](#18)  \n[19\\. NoSuchMethodError in apache-dubbo 2.7.0?](#19)  \n[20.What are the precautions for using AT mode?](#20)  \n[21.Why will the win system have one more empty line for the properties when configured with synchronization script?](#21)  \n[22.What to note for the AT mode and Spring @Transactional annotation hyphenation?](#22)  \n[23.Spring boot 1.5.x appear the Jackson related NoClassDefFoundException?](#23)  \n[24.SpringCloud/HTTP xid cannot transmit?](#24)  \n[25.undo\\_log cannot be deleted after using the mybatis plus dynamic data source component?](#25)  \n[26.Could not found global transaction xid = %s, may be has finished.](#26)  \n[27.Why does TC reported this error: An exceptionCaught() event was fired, and it reached at the tail of the pipeline. It usually means the last handler in the pipeline did not handle the exception?](#27)  \n[28.The database enables automatic update timestamp, which makes dirty data unable to be rolled back?](#28)  \n[29.timeoutrollching occurs before the global transaction timeout?](#29)  \n[30.What database and table splitting solutions does Seata support at this stage?](#30)  \n[31.What are the restrictions on Seata's address registered with the registry?](#31)  \n[32.seata-server cannot be started due to Unrecognized VM option 'CMSParallelRemarkEnabled' Error: Could not create the Java Virtual Machine. Error: A fatal exception has occurred. Program will exit.?](#32)  \n[33\\. What is the scope of SQL support for Seata?](#33)  \n[34\\. What are the JDK version requirements for Seata?](#34)  \n[35\\. When the length of Oracle's NUMBER exceeds 19, entities use Long mapping, which results in the inability to obtain row information, causing undo\\_log to be unable to be inserted and also unable to be rolled back?](#35)  \n[36\\. How to deal with the io.seata.rm.datasource.exec.LockConflictException: get global lock fail ?](#36)  \n[37\\. Why does the java.nio.ByteBuffer.flip()Ljava/nio/ByteBuffer error occur when the client's JDK version is 1.8 when compiling and running ?](#37)  \n[38\\. Why when using Apple M1 chip maven dependence, unable to download the dependence `com.google.protobuf:protoc:exe:3.3.0`?](#38)  \n[39\\. Versions 1.4.2 and below throw \"Cannot construct instance of 'java.time.LocalDateTime'\" when rolling back](#39)  \n[40\\. What are the precautions when Seata-Server uses DB as the storage mode?](#40)  \n[41\\. Did Oracle fail to roll back using the timestamp field type?](#41)  \n[42\\. Did the transaction not roll back after an exception was thrown?](#42)  \n[43\\. How to deal with the @FeignClient annotation url not working and the error prompt \"Load balancer does not have available server for client\"?](#43)  \n[44\\. Why does the error \"pk contains illegal character!\" occur?](#44)  \n[45\\. Why do namingserver and console require JDK 25 for packaging and compiling? & Why are namingserver and console not involved in the compilation and packaging process?](#45)  \n[46\\. Why does Seata report LockWaitTimeoutException due to table name case sensitivity in global transaction lock reentrancy?](#46)  \n\n---\n\n### Q: 1.Can Seata be used in a production environment?\n\n**A:** Since versi"},"sessionId":"ses_16e761ac4ffefZZq0FIZ1eAOKb","timestamp":"2026-06-04T07:30:57.980Z","toolInput":"{\"format\":\"markdown\",\"url\":\"https://seata.apache.org/docs/ove