a is the registry and TC is highly available, how to overwrite Eureka properties at the TC end?](#8)  \n[9.java.lang.NoSuchMethodError: com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.jsontype.TypeSerializer.typeId(Ljava/lang/Object;Lcom/fasterxml/jackson/core/JsonToken;)?](#9)  \n[10\\. Why didn't my mybatis operation return auto-generated ID?](#10)  \n[11.I can't find this package:io.seata.codec.protobuf.generated,and cant't run seata server?](#11)  \n[12.How does TC use database drivers such as mysql/oracle?](#12)  \n[13.Support multiple primary keys?](#13)  \n[14.How to solve the error reported by HikariDataSource?](#14)  \n[15.Can I write the configuration directly to application.properties without using the conf type configuration file?](#15)  \n[16.How to package seata-server after modifying the source code?](#16)  \n[17.What RPC frameworks does seata support now?](#17)  \n[18\\. java.lang.NoSuchMethodError: com.alibaba.druid.sql.ast.statement .SQLSelect.getFirstQueueBlockLcom/alibaba/druid/sql/ast/statement/SQLSelectQueryBlock;](#18)  \n[19\\. NoSuchMethodError in apache-dubbo 2.7.0?](#19)  \n[20.What are the precautions for using AT mode?](#20)  \n[21.Why will the win system have one more empty line for the properties when configured with synchronization script?](#21)  \n[22.What to note for the AT mode and Spring @Transactional annotation hyphenation?](#22)  \n[23.Spring boot 1.5.x appear the Jackson related NoClassDefFoundException?](#23)  \n[24.SpringCloud/HTTP xid cannot transmit?](#24)  \n[25.undo\\_log cannot be deleted after using the mybatis plus dynamic data source component?](#25)  \n[26.Could not found global transaction xid = %s, may be has finished.](#26)  \n[27.Why does TC reported this error: An exceptionCaught() event was fired, and it reached at the tail of the pipeline. It usually means the last handler in the pipeline did not handle the exception?](#27)  \n[28.The database enables automatic update timestamp, which makes dirty data unable to be rolled back?](#28)  \n[29.timeoutrollching occurs before the global transaction timeout?](#29)  \n[30.What database and table splitting solutions does Seata support at this stage?](#30)  \n[31.What are the restrictions on Seata's address registered with the registry?](#31)  \n[32.seata-server cannot be started due to Unrecognized VM option 'CMSParallelRemarkEnabled' Error: Could not create the Java Virtual Machine. Error: A fatal exception has occurred. Program will exit.?](#32)  \n[33\\. What is the scope of SQL support for Seata?](#33)  \n[34\\. What are the JDK version requirements for Seata?](#34)  \n[35\\. When the length of Oracle's NUMBER exceeds 19, entities use Long mapping, which results in the inability to obtain row information, causing undo\\_log to be unable to be inserted and also unable to be rolled back?](#35)  \n[36\\. How to deal with the io.seata.rm.datasource.exec.LockConflictException: get global lock fail ?](#36)  \n[37\\. Why does the java.nio.ByteBuffer.flip()Ljava/nio/ByteBuffer error occur when the client's JDK version is 1.8 when compiling and running ?](#37)  \n[38\\. Why when using Apple M1 chip maven dependence, unable to download the dependence `com.google.protobuf:protoc:exe:3.3.0`?](#38)  \n[39\\. Versions 1.4.2 and below throw \"Cannot construct instance of 'java.time.LocalDateTime'\" when rolling back](#39)  \n[40\\. What are the precautions when Seata-Server uses DB as the storage mode?](#40)  \n[41\\. Did Oracle fail to roll back using the timestamp field type?](#41)  \n[42\\. Did the transaction not roll back after an exception was thrown?](#42)  \n[43\\. How to deal with the @FeignClient annotation url not working and the error prompt \"Load balancer does not have available server for client\"?](#43)  \n[44\\. Why does the error \"pk contains illegal character!\" occur?](#44)  \n[45\\. Why do namingserver and console require JDK 25 for packaging and compiling? & Why are namingserver and console not involved in the compilation and packaging process?](#45)  \n[46\\. Why does Seata report LockWaitTimeoutException due to table name case sensitivity in global transaction lock reentrancy?](#46)  \n\n---\n\n### Q: 1.Can Seata be used in a production environment?\n\n**A:** Since versi"},"obs_mpz6f6kc_3c358c6a5cdd":{"hookType":"post_tool_use","id":"obs_mpz6f6kc_3c358c6a5cdd","raw":{"attachments":[],"call_id":"call_5f00689f5b094d84a5723c72","duration_ms":1141,"metadata":{"truncated":false},"title":"https://seata.apache.org/docs/user/configurations (text/html)","tool_input":"{\"format\":\"markdown\",\"url\":\"https://seata.apache.org/docs/user/configurations\"}","tool_name":"webfetch","tool_output":"  Seata Parameter Configuration | Apache Seata    \n\n[Skip to main content](#__docusaurus_skipToContent_fallback)\n\n[\n\n![Seata Logo](/img/seata_logo.png)![Seata Logo](/img/seata_logo.png)\n\n](/)\n\n[Home](/)\n\n[v2.6](/docs/overview/what-is-seata)\n\n-   [Next Version](/docs/next/user/configurations)\n-   [v2.6](/docs/user/configurations)\n-   [v2.5](/docs/v2.5/user/configurations)\n-   [v2.4](/docs/v2.4/user/configurations)\n-   [v2.3](/docs/v2.3/user/configurations)\n-   [v2.2](/docs/v2.2/user/configurations)\n-   [v2.1](/docs/v2.1/user/configurations)\n-   [v2.0](/docs/v2.0/user/configurations)\n-   [v1.8](/docs/v1.8/user/configurations)\n-   [v1.7](/docs/v1.7/user/configurations)\n-   [v1.6](/docs/v1.6/user/configurations)\n-   [v1.5](/docs/v1.5/user/configurations)\n-   [v1.4](/docs/v1.4/user/configurations)\n-   [v1.3](/docs/v1.3/user/configurations)\n-   [v1.2](/docs/v1.2/user/configurations)\n-   [v1.1](/docs/v1.1/user/configurations)\n-   [v1.0](/docs/v1.0/user/configurations)\n\n[Community](/docs/developers/contributor-guide/new-contributor-guide_dev)[Blog](/blog)[Users](/users)[Download](/download/seata-server)\n\n[Designer](#)\n\n-   [Saga Designer](/saga-designer)\n-   [Saga Designer (Legacy)](/saga-designer-legacy)\n\n[ASF](#)\n\n-   [Foundation](https://www.apache.org)\n-   [License](https://www.apache.org/licenses)\n-   [Events](https://www.apache.org/events/current-event.html)\n-   [Sponsorship](https://www.apache.org/foundation/sponsorship.html)\n-   [Privacy](https://privacy.apache.org/policies/privacy-policy-public.html)\n-   [Security](https://www.apache.org/security)\n-   [Thanks](https://www.apache.org/foundation/thanks.html)\n\n[En](#)\n\n-   [En](/docs/user/configurations)\n-   [õĖŁ](/zh-cn/docs/user/configurations)\n\nSearch\n\n-   Overview\n    \n    -   [What Is Seata?](/docs/overview/what-is-seata)\n    -   [History](/docs/overview/history)\n    -   [Terminology](/docs/overview/terminology)\n    -   [FAQ](/docs/overview/faq)\n-   User Doc\n    \n    -   [Quick Start](/docs/user/quickstart)\n    -   [Seata Parameter Configuration](/docs/user/configurations)\n    -   [Transaction Mode](/docs/user/mode/at)\n        \n    -   [Transactions Grouping](/docs/user/txgroup/transaction-group)\n        \n    -   [Configuration Center](/docs/user/configuration/)\n        \n    -   [Registry Center](/docs/user/registry/)\n        \n    -   [Console](/docs/user/console/introduction)\n        \n    -   [Api Guide](/docs/user/api)\n    -   [Microservice Framework Guide](/docs/user/microservice)\n    -   [ORM Framework Support](/docs/user/ormframework)\n    -   [Data Source support](/docs/user/datasource)\n    -   [SQL Reference](/docs/user/sqlreference/sql-restrictions)\n        \n    -   [APM](/docs/user/apm/skywalking)\n        \n    -   [Testing Report](/docs/user/performance)\n        \n    -   [Appendix](/docs/user/appendix/global-transaction-status)\n        \n-   Developer Guide\n    \n    -   [Transaction Mode](/docs/dev/mode/at-mode)\n        \n    -   [Domain Model](/docs/dev/domain/overviewDomainModel)\n        \n    -   [Metrics Design](/docs/dev/seata-mertics)\n-   Ops Guide\n    \n    -   [Version Upgrade Guide](/docs/ops/upgrade)\n    -   [Multi-configuration Isolation](/docs/ops/multi-configuration-isolation)\n    -   [Deploy](/docs/ops/deploy-guide-beginner)\n        \n-   Security Guide\n    \n    -   [SecretKey Security](/docs/security/secret-key)\n\n-   [](/)\n-   User Doc\n-   Seata Parameter Configuration\n\nVersion: v2.6\n\nOn this page\n\n# The Seata Parameter Configuration\n\n### Change record[ŌĆŗ](#change-record \"Direct link to Change record\")\n\n```\n20201216(1.6.0):The change records of configuration items from 1.4.0 to 1.6.0 are no longer maintained in a centralized manner. Please check the changes of relevant versions separately according to the configuration items20200716(1.3.0):1. Added the relevant configuration of store.redis2. The nacos registry configuration group item has been added, and the values of the Server and Client must be consistent3. Add the client.rm.sagaBranchRegisterEnable configuration item, which is false by default20200421(1.2.0):1. Add the registry.nacos.application attribute. The default value is seata server. The values on the server and client sides must be consistent20200220(1.1.0):1. The formats in the file.conf and registry.conf configuration files are uniformly converted to the hump format2. Unify the default values of all configuration files (file.conf, registry.conf, seata spring boot starter)3. Optimize the configuration of transaction grouping and TC cluster in seata spring boot starter4. Remove client.support.spring.datasource.autoproxy and add @ EnableAutoDataSourceProxy5. Add server.rollbackRetryTimeoutUnlockEnable configuration item, which is false by default6. Add the transport.shutdown.wait configuration item. The default is 3 secondsThe annotation is used to enable the automatic proxy of the data source, and the proxy implementation method can be selected (see Appendix 5 for details)20191221:1. Add seata.enabled, client.report.success.enabletransport.enable-client-batch-send-requestŃĆüclient.log.exceptionRate\n```\n\n## Attention attribute (see all attributes for detailed description)[ŌĆŗ](#attention-attribute-see-all-attributes-for-detailed-description \"Direct link to Attention attribute (see all attributes for detailed description)\")\n\nServer side\n\nclient side\n\nregistry.type\n\nregistry.type\n\nconfig.type\n\nconfig.type\n\n#store.mode=db requires the following configuration\n\nservice.vgroupMapping.my\\* test\\* tx\\_ group\n\nstore.db.driverClassName\n\nservice.default. grouplist\n\nstore.db.url\n\nservice. disableGlobalTransaction\n\nstore.db.user\n\nstore.db.password\n\n#store.mode=Redis requires the following configurations\n\nstore.redis.host\n\nstore.redis.port\n\nstore.redis.database\n\nstore.redis.password\n\n#The following configurations are required for \"store.mode=raft\"\n\nserver.raft.group\n\nserver.raft.server-addr\n\nserver.raft.snapshot-interval\n\n## All attributes[ŌĆŗ](#all-attributes \"Direct link to All attributes\")\n\n### Public sector[ŌĆŗ](#public-sector \"Direct link to Public sector\")\n\nkey\n\ndesc\n\nremark\n\nchange record\n\ntransport.type\n\nSocket communication mode\n\nTCP, UNIX\\* DOMAIN\\* SOCKET, default TCP\n\ntransport.server\n\nsocket channel type\n\nNIO, NATIVE (select KQueue or Epoll according to the operating system type and socket communication mode. Note that Windows only supports NIO, and NATIVE mode will throw an exception)\n\ntransport.enableTmClientBatchSendRequest\n\nTM Batch Send Request Message Switch\n\nDefault false\n\nnew in 1.5.1 version\n\ntransport.enableRmClientBatchSendRequest\n\nRM Batch Send Request Message Switch\n\nDefault true\n\nnew in 1.5.1 version\n\ntransport.enableTcServerBatchSendResponse\n\nTC Batch Send Reply Message Switch\n\nDefault false\n\nnew in 1.5.1 version\n\ntransport.rpcRmRequestTimeout\n\nRM sending request timeout\n\n15 seconds by default\n\nnew in 1.5.1 version\n\ntransport.rpcTmRequestTimeout\n\nTM sending request timeout\n\n30 seconds by default\n\nnew in 1.5.1 version\n\ntransport.rpcTcRequestTimeout\n\nTC sending request timeout\n\n15 seconds by default\n\nnew in 1.5.1 version\n\ntransport.threadFactory. bossThreadSize\n\nNetty communication model Boss group threads\n\nDefault 1\n\ntransport.threadFactory. workerThreadSize\n\nNetty communication model Worker group threads\n\nThe number of threads can be configured or the number of threads in a specific thread working mode can be selected. There are four default working modes of threads: Auto (2 \\_ CPU cores+1), Pin (CPU cores, applicable to computing intensive tasks), BusyPin (CPU cores+1, applicable to computing intensive and memory limited scenarios) Default (2 \\_ CPU cores, applicable to IO intensive tasks), the default value is Default mode\n\ntransport.shutdown. wait\n\nTime to wait for service offline before the Netty thread pool on the server is closed\n\n3 seconds by default\n\ntransport.serialization\n\nClient and server communication codec method\n\nseata (ByteBuf), protobuf, kryo, hessian, default seata\n\ntransport.compressor\n\nCompression method of communication data between client and"},"sessionId":"ses_16e761ac4ffefZZq0FIZ1eAOKb","timestamp":"2026-06-04T07:31:10.713Z","toolInput":"{\"format\":\"markdown\",\"url\":\"https://seata.apache.org/docs/user/configurations\"}","toolName":"webfetch","toolOutput":"  Seata Parameter Configuration | Apache Seata    \n\n[Skip to main content](#__docusaurus_skipToContent_fallback)\n\n[\n\n![Seata Logo](/img/seata_logo.png)![Seata Logo](/img/seata_logo.png)\n\n](/)\n\n[Home](/)\n\n[v2.6](/docs/overview/what-is-seata)\n\n-   [Next Version](/docs/next/user/configurations)\n-   [v2.6](/docs/user/configurations)\n-   [v2.5](/docs/v2.5/user/configurations)\n-   [v2.4](/docs/v2.4/user/configurations)\n-   [v2.3](/docs/v2.3/user/configurations)\n-   [v2.2](/docs/v2.2/user/configurations)\n-   [v2.1](/docs/v2.1/user/configurations)\n-   [v2.0](/docs/v2.0/user/configurations)\n-   [v1.8](/docs/v1.8/user/configurations)\n-   [v1.7](/docs/v1.7/user/configurations)\n-   [v1.6](/docs/v1.6/user/configurations)\n-   [v1.5](/docs/v1.5/user/configurations)\n-   [v1.4](/docs/v1.4/user/